Package dog.giraffe.points

Classes to describe vectors and lists of vectors. All vectors are in some Euclidean space.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Points.Classification<C>
    A callback interface with the result of the nearest center calculation.
    Points.ForEach
    A callback interface for the enumeration of all of the vectors in a Points.
    Sum
    Instances of Sum represents the sum of a mutable list of double values.
    Sum.Factory
    Factory for Sums.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayPoints<T>
    A MutablePoints backed by a primitive array.
    Deviation
    Instances of Deviation represents the statistical deviation of a mutable list of vectors.
    Deviation.Factory
    Factory for Deviations.
    Distance
    Helpers methods related to the standard Euclidean distance function.
    FloatArrayPoints
    A MutablePoints backed by a float array.
    KDTree
    A Points implementation which is a binary tree over a backing MutablePoints.
    Mean
    Instances of Mean represents the statistical mean of a mutable list of vectors.
    Mean.Factory
    Factory for Means.
    MeanDouble
    Instances of MeanDouble represents the statistical mean of a mutable list of values.
    MutablePoints
    A mutable list of vectors.
    MutablePoints.Interval
    An interval of indices.
    Points
    A list of vectors.
    Sum.SingleVariable  
    UnsignedByteArrayPoints
    A MutablePoints backed by a byte array.
    UnsignedShortArrayPoints
    A MutablePoints backed by a short array.
    Vector
    Mutable representation of a vector in Euclidean space.
    VectorList
    A List of Vectors.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    EmptySetException
    Thrown when an operation is not defined on empty sets, like Mean.mean().
